 this kind of embodied and performative analysis should be more widely conducted in studies of popular politics worldwide.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical participationzChina. 0aProtest movementszChina. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aSociology : Social Change. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847622340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438476223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438476223/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles